{"id": 194, "date": "2018-01-12T06:00:33", "date_gmt": "2018-01-12T14:00:33", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=194"}, "modified": "2020-11-24T21:53:46", "modified_gmt": "2020-11-25T05:53:46", "slug": "meeting-across-the-river-bruce-springsteen-and-rosanne-cash", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2018/01/12/meeting-across-the-river-bruce-springsteen-and-rosanne-cash/", "title": {"rendered": "Meeting Across the River: Bruce Springsteen and Rosanne Cash, Sea of Heartbreak"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>&#8220;Sea of Heartbreak&#8221; first became a hit in 1961, when Don Gibson took it all the way to #2 on the Billboard Hot Country Singles chart.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"DON GIBSON:  Sea Of Heartbreak\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/A4bo4ByFhLM?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>It charted again eleven years later, when Kenny Price took it to #24.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Kenny Price &quot;Sea Of Heartbreak&quot;\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/PDplFSIA0Bw?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>&#8230;and again in 1989, when Ronnie McDowell took it to #39, marking three consecutive decades for with Top 40 country status for &#8220;Sea of Heartbreak.&#8221;</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Sea Of Heartbreak\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/aCyZStpJzXY?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>If only Johnny Cash had released it as a single when he recorded it for his 1996\u00a0<em>Unchained\u00a0</em>album, &#8220;Sea of Heartbreak&#8221; might have charted for <em>four</em> consecutive decades.</p>\n<p>He didn&#8217;t though, and the streak ended. But that didn&#8217;t stop Cash&#8217;s daughter Rosanne from taking a run at it herself in 2009.</p>\n<p>Well, not exactly by herself.\u00a0From Cash&#8217;s album, <em>The List, </em>here&#8217;s &#8220;Sea of Heartbreak&#8221; with Bruce Springsteen.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"ROSANNE CASH (with BRUCE SPRINGSTEEN) - Sea Of Heartbreak (2009)\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/A3LSrcKksCo?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>Rosanne and Bruce performed &#8220;Sea of Heartbreak&#8221; together just once, at Rosanne&#8217;s show in Durham, North Carolina in 2010. No recording circulates from that performance.</p>\n<p><strong>Sea of Heartbreak<br />\nRecorded:</strong> ?<br />\n<strong>Released:\u00a0</strong><em>The List</em> (2009)<br />\n<strong>First performed:</strong> April 15, 2010 (Durham, NC)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> April 15, 2010 (Durham, NC)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>&#8220;Sea of Heartbreak&#8221; first became a hit in 1961, when Don Gibson took it all the way to #2 on the Billboard Hot Country Singles&hellip;</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 195, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standa